The Country Programme Action Plan 2005-2011 for St. Vincent and the Grenadines identified the following key Programme Component Results under the Thematic area of Poverty Reduction.
a)	Establishment and operationalisation of a comprehensive poverty and MDG monitoring system, including living conditions surveys such as the Core Welfare Indicators Questionnaire (CWIQ) Survey; 
b)	Professionals in the public sector and academia trained in data collection, analysis, monitoring and evaluation of social phenomena;
c)	Poverty Reduction Strategy Paper (PRSP) finalised with gender, HIV/AIDS, disaster risk reduction, and environmental issues mainstreamed;  
d)	New initiatives implemented to promote economic diversification and reduce poverty through entrepreneurial activities; and 
e)	Six (6) community centres equipped to provide access to internet, and ICT skills training to improve employment opportunities for the rural poor

